Full regressions passed on a workstation last night, so there were no plan changes in the regress tests.
Do not merge this yet. I intend to change it to address the divisioning column also.

I think there is a problem with this change. It is not sufficient stand-alone.

I have recently tested installation, and trafstart failed because the classpath did not get refreshed after installation of TRX files in HBase.

I suggest that a good time to remove the cached file (to update the cache) is not necessarily at installation time, but at trafodion start time.  Just in case HBase changed something since we previously started.

The rework contains two more changes:

1. I implemented @zellerh 's suggestion to skip divisioning columns also when computing index compatibility.
2. The unit tests for this encountered a core in GenPreCode.cpp, where the ValueId for the divisioning column was not in the MapTable when the plan was generated against an index. @nonstop-qfchen encountered this bug also and suggested a fix; @zellerh reworked this fix, offering a change to optimizer/ItemExpr.cpp. This rework includes the latter change, along with changes to regression test compGeneral/TEST071 to exercise this code path. Thanks to @zellerh and @nonstop-qfchen for this change.

I will re-run full regressions overnight on a workstation before merging this change.
Full regressions run on a workstation passed overnight.
